c: 6
v: 148
t: "Those who associate [others in their worship of God) will say: ´I God had so wished, neither we nor our forefathers would have associated [anything with Him] nor have forbidden anything.\" Even so did those before them reject [Us] until they tasted Our might. SAY: \"Have you (all) any knowledge? Then bring it here for us! Why, you only follow conjecture; you are merely guessing"